TITLE: My First Childhood Experience & Blessings Of Baba Balak Nath | P2
VIDEO: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sebJTnYQkSU
DATE: March 11, 2026 (recording date); events described span 1984-1992
LANGUAGE: Hindi (auto-translated)

SUMMARY:
In Part 2 of the series, Maa Noor Ananta continues the narrative from where Part 1 left off. After the cosmic snake incident and the withdrawal from normal life, her academic performance deteriorated severely. She failed Class 8 because her mind could not focus on studies -- even when she tried hard and studied, she would forget everything during exams because "something else was happening" alongside her. She became increasingly isolated from family, stopped eating (going hungry for days), remained sad and silent, and would lie quietly in her room. Her parents grew deeply worried.

During this troubled period, she developed an intense, unexplainable urge to go to Punjab. The pull was so strong that she felt she could fly there. She had no logical reason -- she didn't know who was calling her or why -- but the restlessness was overwhelming. Then suddenly, she fell seriously ill and went into a coma. She was admitted to a local hospital in Namrup (Assam), but doctors could not diagnose the problem. She was referred to Dibrugarh, but even there no treatment worked. Doctors ran all tests but could find nothing wrong, and eventually told the family to take her home, saying treatment was not possible.

After bringing her home, her mother was divinely triggered to organize a kirtan (devotional singing ceremony) at home. Remarkably, what hospitals and doctors in Namrup and Dibrugarh could not achieve over many days, the kirtan accomplished -- she regained consciousness during the devotional singing. Everyone called it a miracle and a blessing of Devi Maa. Immediately upon regaining consciousness, in a semi-aware state, she removed her gold earrings (mundre/baliyan) and offered them to Baba Balak Nath's altar in their home. This act triggered her father's attention -- especially significant because there is a traditional belief that girls do not visit Baba Balak Nath's shrine. This pattern was being broken.

She reveals she was born in 1971 in Namrup, Assam. She spent 1971 to 1991 in Assam. In 1991-92, driven by her persistent demand to go to Punjab, the family permanently shifted from Namrup, Assam to Ludhiana, Punjab. Here she met "Shaili" (her life partner), and her real karmic life and sadhana (spiritual practice) began. She emphasizes that she has been in this spiritual process since then, never took help from anyone, healed herself, and is entirely self-made. She understood her life's purpose by 2010 and has been fully aware and on her journey since 2008.

KEY REVELATIONS:
- Failed Class 8 due to spiritual awakening disrupting normal cognitive function -- classic sign of kundalini activation overwhelming the mind
- Went into an unexplained coma that no medical science could diagnose or treat -- no tests revealed any abnormality
- Was healed by kirtan (devotional singing), not by medical treatment -- divine intervention through sacred sound vibration
- Upon regaining consciousness, her first act was offering her gold earrings to Baba Balak Nath -- an unconscious devotional act guided by higher consciousness
- The traditional pattern that "girls don't go to Baba Balak Nath" was broken through her -- a Yug Parivartan pattern-breaking event
- The intense pull toward Punjab was a cosmic relocation guided by destiny -- "sthan parivartan" (change of place) was happening
- She declares "I am my own guru" -- all learning came from life experiences, not external teachers
- Life purpose became clear in 2010; full surrender to the spiritual path happened in 2008
- Born in Namrup, Assam in 1971; shifted permanently to Ludhiana, Punjab in 1991

KEY REVELATIONS (continued):
- She briefly explored modeling around 2004 but all life events were steering her toward her current spiritual mission
- Did a small telefilm role in Jammu involving a snake character -- cosmic synchronicity with her childhood snake experience
- She has never taken any painkillers, sleeping pills, or medication -- no concept of depression; heals everything through self-awareness
- Emphasizes the critical difference between "dharm" (religious rituals/puja) and "adhyatm" (true spirituality/inner journey)

TIMELINE EVENTS:
- 1971: Born in Namrup, Assam
- 1984: Cosmic snake event and spiritual awakening triggered (from Part 1)
- ~1985-1986: Failed Class 8 due to inability to focus on studies
- ~1986-1987: Fell into an unexplained coma; hospitalized in Namrup, referred to Dibrugarh, doctors unable to diagnose
- ~1986-1987: Healed through kirtan at home; offered gold earrings to Baba Balak Nath upon regaining consciousness
- 1991-1992: Family permanently shifted from Namrup, Assam to Ludhiana, Punjab
- Post-1992: Met Shaili (life partner) in Punjab; karmic life and spiritual sadhana began in earnest
- ~2004: Brief attraction to modeling line
- 2008: Full clarity and surrender to spiritual path
- 2010: Life purpose fully understood

ORIGINAL HINDI KEY QUOTES:
- "मैं क्लास एट में फेल हो जाती हूं क्योंकि अब मेरा मन ही नहीं लग रहा पढ़ाई में" = "I failed Class 8 because my mind was simply not engaged in studies anymore"
- "मैं कोमा में चली गई, एकदम से सडन पता नहीं क्या हो गया" = "I went into a coma, suddenly, don't know what happened"
- "डॉक्टरों को कुछ भी समझ में नहीं आ रहा है, सारे टेस्ट कर लिए" = "Doctors could not understand anything, all tests were done"
- "कीर्तन चलते हुए मुझे होश आया, एकदम से मैं इतने दिनों बाद होश में आई" = "During the kirtan I regained consciousness, suddenly after so many days I came to my senses"
- "मुझे ऐसा हो रहा था कि बस कुछ ऐसा हो जाए मैं उड़ के चली जाऊं, पंजाब पहुंच जाऊं" = "I felt like something should happen so I could just fly away and reach Punjab"
- "जो लिखा होता है वही होना होता है" = "What is written (in destiny) is what must happen"
- "वो ब्लेसिंग थी मुझे शेरावली मां की, बाबा बालकनाथ की, शिवा की, कृष्णा की" = "That was a blessing from Sherawali Maa, Baba Balak Nath, Shiva, and Krishna"
- "आई एम माय ओन गुरु क्योंकि मैंने जो सीखा है ना वो अपनी खुद के जिंदगी से सीखा है" = "I am my own guru because what I have learned, I learned from my own life"

YUG PARIVARTAN ASPECT: This part reveals the intense purification and karmic preparation phase of the Yug Parivartan soul. The unexplained coma represents a deep spiritual transformation that transcended medical science -- the soul was being recalibrated. The healing through kirtan (not medicine) establishes the supremacy of divine energy over material science. The breaking of the "girls don't visit Baba Balak Nath" tradition foreshadows the larger pattern-breaking of Yug Parivartan. The cosmic relocation from Assam to Punjab was divinely orchestrated -- Punjab being the destined ground for the next phase of the mission. The emphasis on self-realization without external gurus aligns with the Yug Parivartan teaching that true awakening comes from within.


